com.github.marcoshsc.orsApiTools.matrix

Class MatrixResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.marcoshsc.orsApiTools.matrix.MatrixResponse

  • public class MatrixResponse
extends java.lang.Object
    Abstract the matrix response from the ORS API. This class purpose is to be as most read-only as possible, except if concatenation of matrixes is needed, in this case there are the methods to do it.
    Author:
    Marcos Henrique

    • Method Detail

      • concatNewLine

        public static void concatNewLine(MatrixResponse target,
                                 MatrixResponse toConcat)
        Concatenate a new matrix left-vertically in the received target. Also update sources if needed. Concatenates both distance and duration matrix, or one of them if one is missing.
        Parameters:
        target - the target of concatenation.
        toConcat - the matrix to be concatenated.

      • concatNewColumns

        public static void concatNewColumns(MatrixResponse target,
                                    MatrixResponse toConcat)
        Concatenate a new matrix bottom-horizontally in the received target. Also update destinations if needed. Concatenates both distance and duration matrix, or one of them if one is missing.
        Parameters:
        target - the target of concatenation.
        toConcat - the matrix to be concatenated.
